Story: 1/1;
Writing/Screenplay: 1/1;Total Base Score = 5Modifiers (+ or -):
Originality: +0.5 (Although this is a typical war drama, it is my opinion that we need more films about WW1, or 'The Great War'.);Cinematography: +1 (Toward the end of the film there are great shots of predawn skylight, which has been hard to accurately capture until recent technological advancements.);Standout Performances: +0 (Nothing in this movie "stands out".);Total RealReview Rating: 6.5 (rounded up to 7 for IMDB)

Well, the Story is quite simple;
the script is OK;
of course, the actors are just great;but what makes this movie so very special is the camera!Just fantastic work!
If this would have been WITHOUT the impressive camera work, I´d say its a 7 out of 10 stars...
But they just packed the 9 stars for "forcing me to watch without blinking"!
It´s been very long, since I was so impressed.
